-- China to keep reforming yuan mechanism: U.S. official
-- 
-- Thu Sep 23, 2010 2:41pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/09/23/us-usa-china-yuan-exchange-idUSTRE68M4I620100923

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Chinese Premier Wen Jiabao on Thursday told President Barack that China would press ahead with the reforming the exchange rate rules for his country's yuan currency, a senior U.S. official said. 

 "Premier Wen did reiterate the Chinese intention to ... continue with reform of their exchange rate mechanism," Jeffrey Bader, the senior National Security Council official for Asia told reporters after Wen and Obama met in New York. (Reporting by  Steve Holland ; Writing by  Louis Charbonneau )